Usain Bolt has revealed he wants to smash his own 200-metre world record by running the distance in under 19 seconds and insists he is almost impossible to beat when he is fully fit .
The six-time Olympic gold medallist is currently in Rio de Janeiro , acclimatising ahead of next year 's Olympic Games in the Brazilian capital , and will compete in the ` Mano a Mano ' 100-metat on Sunday .
The Jamaican sprinter ran the 200 metres in 19.19 sec at the 2009 World Championships in Berlin .